# Sync published posts (Instagram · vault · website)

When adding or updating **published** Athas social posts, update **all three** places in the same turn. Never update only the website or only the vault.

## Sources of truth

| Layer | Location |
|---|---|
| Live feed | https://www.instagram.com/athas.band |
| Vault archive | `/mnt/c/Users/lucas/source/extracted_yt/1/Anglos-Vault/` (`Post - *.md` + `Social media pipeline.md`) |
| Website | `src/content/updates/*.md(x)` + covers in `src/assets/updates/` |

## Checklist for every newly published post

1. **Instagram** — Confirm permalink, format (`post` / `carousel` / `reel`), publish date, and live caption (fetch profile API or ask the user).
2. **Vault** — Create or promote a `Post - … (Instagram).md` note:
   - Set `**Status:** published`, `**Published:**`, `**URL:**`, `**Post id:**`, `**Format:**`
   - Paste the live caption under `## Published caption`
   - Prefer updating an existing draft/ready note over creating a duplicate
   - Append a row to the Published table in `Social media pipeline.md`
3. **Website** — Add `src/content/updates/YYYY-MM-DD-slug.md` with frontmatter (`title`, `date`, `summary`, `coverImage`, `instagramUrl`, `format`, `coverAlt`) and a short polished body (canonical **Wesaþ** spelling).
4. **Cover** — Save the feed thumbnail (or a better still) to `src/assets/updates/YYYY-MM-DD-slug.{jpg,webp}` and point `coverImage` at it.

## Mapping conventions

- Vault note: `Post - [Title] (Instagram).md` or `(Instagram reel).md`
- Website slug: `YYYY-MM-DD-kebab-title.md` matching the cover filename stem
- Instagram URL field on the site: `instagramUrl` (optional `instagramReelUrl` when both exist)

## Do not

- Ship website-only or vault-only updates for a live Instagram post
- Leave vault notes as `draft` / `ready` after they are live
- Invent permalinks or captions — use the live post
